exports[`create-tinybase > ts-react-chat-node > should match snapshot 1`] = `
{
  "README.md": "# test-ts-react-chat-node

A TinyBase app built with TypeScript and React.

## Getting Started

Alongside this file, you will see a directory called \`client\` (and one called \`server\` for your local Node.js server).

To start the web client with Vite, run the following commands:

\`\`\`bash
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
\`\`\`

PNPM, Yarn, and Bun should also work. Your app will be available at
\`http://localhost:5173\`, or whichever port Vite specifies in the console.

If you included server code, start the server in a separate terminal, ideally
before starting the client:

\`\`\`bash
# In a separate terminal
cd server
npm install
npm run dev
\`\`\`

After that, start hacking!

## Structure

This project is organized into two main directories:

### Client

The \`client\` directory contains your React-based web application,
built with Vite and TypeScript.

#### Key Files

- **\`index.html\`**: The main HTML file that loads your app
- **\`src/index.tsx\`**: Entry point that bootstraps and renders the React app
- **\`src/App.tsx\`**: Main React component that renders the chat interface
- **\`src/ChatStore.tsx\`**: TinyBase chat messages store configuration
  - **\`src/SettingsStore.tsx\`**: TinyBase settings store (not synchronized)
- **\`src/config.tsx\`**: Configuration settings (including server connection URL)

#### How It Works

The app uses **TinyBase** to manage application state in a reactive data store.

The store is a **MergeableStore**, which supports real-time synchronization across
multiple clients. When you open the app, it generates a unique room ID in the URL
path (e.g., \`/abc123\`). Anyone who visits the same URL will share the same data
and see live updates from other users.

**Persistence** is enabled using browser LocalStorage.
Your data is automatically saved and restored when you reload the page.

**Synchronization** is powered by TinyBase's WebSocket synchronizer, connecting
to your Node.js server.
When data changes locally, it's sent to the server and broadcast to all other
clients in the same room. The MergeableStore handles conflict resolution using
CRDTs, ensuring all clients converge to the same state.

**React Integration**: TinyBase provides React hooks that automatically subscribe
to store changes and trigger re-renders when data updates. This means your UI
stays in sync with your data with minimal boilerplate.

Components like \`MessageList\` and \`MessageInput\` use TinyBase hooks to display and send messages
to interact
with the store.

### Server

The \`server\` directory contains your Node.js WebSocket server.

#### Key Files

- **\`index.tsx\`**: Server entry point

#### How It Works

    The server runs a **Node.js WebSocket server** using the \`ws\` library. It acts
    as a relay between clients, broadcasting state changes to all connected clients
    in the same room.

    When a client connects to a path (e.g., \`/abc123\`), the server groups them with
    other clients on the same path and ensures all changes are synchronized.

    The server logs when clients join or leave rooms, helping you monitor activity
    during development.

## Learn More

- [TinyBase Documentation](https://tinybase.org)
- [TinyBase Examples](https://tinybase.org/demos/)
",
  "client/.npmrc": "legacy-peer-deps=true
",
  "client/index.html": "<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;800&display=swap"
    />

    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>TinyBase Chat</title>
    <style>
      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        user-select: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      body {
        --hue: 270;
        --fg: oklch(85% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --fg2: oklch(60% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg: oklch(20% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg2: oklch(25% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --border: oklch(30% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg-header: oklch(30% 0.008 var(--hue) / 0.5);
        --accent: #d81b60;
        color: var(--fg);
        background: var(--bg);
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      }

      #appContainer {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      #app {
        max-width: 60rem;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div id="appContainer"></div>

    <script type="module" src="/src/index.tsx"></script>
  </body>
</html>
",
