exports[`create-tinybase > ts-svelte-drawing-sqlite > should match snapshot 1`] = `
{
  "README.md": "# test-ts-svelte-drawing-sqlite

A TinyBase app built with TypeScript and Svelte.

## Getting Started

Alongside this file, you will see a directory called \`client\`.

To start the web client with Vite, run the following commands:

\`\`\`bash
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
\`\`\`

PNPM, Yarn, and Bun should also work. Your app will be available at
\`http://localhost:5173\`, or whichever port Vite specifies in the console.

After that, start hacking!

## Structure

This project is organized into a single \`client\` directory:

### Client

The \`client\` directory contains your Svelte-based web application,
built with Vite and TypeScript.

#### Key Files

- **\`index.html\`**: The main HTML file that loads your app
- **\`src/index.ts\`**: Entry point that bootstraps and mounts the Svelte app
- **\`src/App.svelte\`**: Main Svelte component that renders the drawing canvas
- **\`src/canvasStore.ts\`**: TinyBase drawing canvas store configuration
  - **\`src/settingsStore.ts\`**: TinyBase settings store (not synchronized)
- **\`src/config.ts\`**: Configuration settings

#### How It Works

The app uses **TinyBase** to manage application state in a reactive data store.

**Persistence** is enabled using SQLite WASM (running entirely in the browser).
Your data is automatically saved and restored when you reload the page.

**Svelte Integration**: TinyBase provides Svelte stores and helpers that keep the
UI reactive as data changes. Components subscribe declaratively so the interface
stays synchronized with the underlying TinyBase store.

## Learn More

- [TinyBase Documentation](https://tinybase.org)
- [TinyBase Examples](https://tinybase.org/demos/)
",
  "client/.npmrc": "legacy-peer-deps=true
",
  "client/index.html": "<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;800&display=swap"
    />

    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>TinyBase Drawing</title>
    <style>
      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        user-select: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      body {
        --hue: 270;
        --fg: oklch(85% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --fg2: oklch(60% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg: oklch(20% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg2: oklch(25% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --border: oklch(30% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg-header: oklch(30% 0.008 var(--hue) / 0.5);
        --accent: #d81b60;
        color: var(--fg);
        background: var(--bg);
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      }

      #appContainer {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      #app {
        max-width: 60rem;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div id="appContainer">
      <div id="topBarMount"></div>
      <div id="app"></div>
    </div>

    <script type="module" src="/src/index.ts"></script>
  </body>
</html>
