exports[`create-tinybase > ts-svelte-todos-remote-sync > should match snapshot 1`] = `
{
  "README.md": "# test-ts-svelte-todos-remote-sync

A TinyBase app built with TypeScript and Svelte.

## Getting Started

Alongside this file, you will see a directory called \`client\`.

To start the web client with Vite, run the following commands:

\`\`\`bash
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
\`\`\`

PNPM, Yarn, and Bun should also work. Your app will be available at
\`http://localhost:5173\`, or whichever port Vite specifies in the console.

After that, start hacking!

## Structure

This project is organized into a single \`client\` directory:

### Client

The \`client\` directory contains your Svelte-based web application,
built with Vite and TypeScript.

#### Key Files

- **\`index.html\`**: The main HTML file that loads your app
- **\`src/index.ts\`**: Entry point that bootstraps and mounts the Svelte app
- **\`src/App.svelte\`**: Main Svelte component that renders the todo list
- **\`src/store.ts\`**: TinyBase main store configuration
- **\`src/config.ts\`**: Configuration settings

#### How It Works

The app uses **TinyBase** to manage application state in a reactive data store.

The store is a **MergeableStore**, which supports real-time synchronization across
multiple clients. When you open the app, it generates a unique room ID in the URL
path (e.g., \`/abc123\`). Anyone who visits the same URL will share the same data
and see live updates from other users.

**Persistence** is enabled using browser LocalStorage.
Your data is automatically saved and restored when you reload the page.

**Synchronization** is powered by TinyBase's WebSocket synchronizer (connecting to a demo server at vite.tinybase.org).
When data changes locally, it's sent to the server and broadcast to all other
clients in the same room. The MergeableStore handles conflict resolution using
CRDTs, ensuring all clients converge to the same state.

**Svelte Integration**: TinyBase provides Svelte stores and helpers that keep the
UI reactive as data changes. Components subscribe declaratively so the interface
stays synchronized with the underlying TinyBase store.

## Learn More

- [TinyBase Documentation](https://tinybase.org)
- [TinyBase Examples](https://tinybase.org/demos/)
",
  "client/.npmrc": "legacy-peer-deps=true
",
  "client/index.html": "<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;800&display=swap"
    />

    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>TinyBase Todos</title>
    <style>
      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        user-select: none;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

      body {
        --hue: 270;
        --fg: oklch(85% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --fg2: oklch(60% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg: oklch(20% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg2: oklch(25% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --border: oklch(30% 0.01 var(--hue));
        --bg-header: oklch(30% 0.008 var(--hue) / 0.5);
        --accent: #d81b60;
        color: var(--fg);
        background: var(--bg);
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      }

      #appContainer {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        min-height: 100vh;
      }

      #app {
        max-width: 60rem;
        width: 100%;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div id="appContainer">
      <div id="topBarMount"></div>
      <div id="app"></div>
    </div>

    <script type="module" src="/src/index.ts"></script>
  </body>
</html>
